{% extends "layouts/base.njk" %}
{% import "partials/_demo.njk" as ui %}

{% block title %}Empty state · Stisla{% endblock %}

{% block content %}
  <header>
    <h1>Empty state</h1>
    <p class="lead">A centered block shown in place of content that is absent.</p>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic</h2>
    <p>An empty state pairs a <code>.empty-state__media</code> slot with a <code>.empty-state__title</code> and an optional <code>.empty-state__text</code>. By default the media is a soft circle holding a single icon. Only the title is required.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="empty-state">
      <span class="empty-state__media"><i data-lucide="inbox"></i></span>
      <h3 class="empty-state__title">No messages</h3>
      <p class="empty-state__text">Your inbox is empty. New messages will show up here.</p>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>With actions</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.empty-state__action</code> to move the person forward. The slot centers and wraps its controls, so a primary plus a secondary action stacks cleanly on a narrow region.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="empty-state">
      <span class="empty-state__media"><i data-lucide="folder-plus"></i></span>
      <h3 class="empty-state__title">No projects yet</h3>
      <p class="empty-state__text">Create your first project to start organizing your work.</p>
      <div class="empty-state__action">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--primary"><i data-lucide="plus"></i> New project</button>
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--neutral btn--outline">Import</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Tone</h2>
    <p>Add a <code>.empty-state--*</code> tone to color the media for a fixed meaning. Use <code>danger</code> for an error and <code>success</code> for a done state. Since empty means the region is empty of its expected content, an error page is an empty state too. The title and text stay neutral so the message reads as text, not color.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <div class="empty-state empty-state--danger">
        <span class="empty-state__media"><i data-lucide="triangle-alert"></i></span>
        <h3 class="empty-state__title">Something went wrong</h3>
        <p class="empty-state__text">We could not load this page. Try again in a moment.</p>
        <div class="empty-state__action">
          <button type="button" class="btn btn--danger"><i data-lucide="rotate-cw"></i> Retry</button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="empty-state empty-state--success">
        <span class="empty-state__media"><i data-lucide="check"></i></span>
        <h3 class="empty-state__title">All caught up</h3>
        <p class="empty-state__text">You have cleared every task in this list.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Compact</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.empty-state--compact</code> for an empty region inside a card, a panel, or an empty table body, where a full-size empty state would dominate. It shrinks the media and tightens the padding.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="card" style="max-width: 24rem;">
      <div class="card__header">
        <h3 class="card__title">Recent activity</h3>
      </div>
      <div class="card__body">
        <div class="empty-state empty-state--compact">
          <span class="empty-state__media"><i data-lucide="activity"></i></span>
          <h3 class="empty-state__title">No activity yet</h3>
          <p class="empty-state__text">Actions you take will appear here.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Bordered</h2>
    <p>Add <code>.empty-state--bordered</code> for a dashed region box, the common look for a droppable or fillable area like an empty board column or an upload target. The border follows the tone when one is set.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="empty-state empty-state--bordered" style="max-width: 28rem;">
      <span class="empty-state__media"><i data-lucide="upload"></i></span>
      <h3 class="empty-state__title">Drop files to upload</h3>
      <p class="empty-state__text">Or browse from your computer. PNG, JPG, or PDF up to 10 MB.</p>
      <div class="empty-state__action">
        <button type="button" class="btn btn--neutral btn--outline">Browse files</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Media</h2>
    <p>The media slot hosts more than a bare icon. Drop in an <code>.icon-box</code>, an <code>.avatar</code>, or a <code>.spinner</code> and the slot sheds its own circle so the media is never double-framed. A spinner suits a region that is loading toward empty.</p>
    {% call ui.demo() %}
    <div class="d-flex flex-wrap gap-4">
      <div class="empty-state empty-state--compact">
        <span class="empty-state__media">
          <span class="icon-box icon-box--primary icon-box--round icon-box--roomy"><i data-lucide="users"></i></span>
        </span>
        <h3 class="empty-state__title">No team members</h3>
        <p class="empty-state__text">Invite people to collaborate.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="empty-state empty-state--compact">
        <span class="empty-state__media"><span class="spinner" aria-hidden="true"></span></span>
        <h3 class="empty-state__title">Loading</h3>
        <p class="empty-state__text">Fetching your latest data.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    {% endcall %}
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>With an illustration</h2>
    <p>For a richer empty state, pair it with an <a href="/illustrations">illustration</a> in the media slot. The slot sheds its circle and caps the art width, so the spot art sits on its own. See the <a href="/illustrations">Illustrations</a> page for the full set and how to re-tone them.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Customization</h2>
    <p>These variables retune <code>.empty-state</code> without touching component CSS. Set them on the empty state, on a parent scope, or on <code>:root</code>. The tone reads on a single block, which is how the tone modifiers and a one-off override work.</p>

    <h3>Layout</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Variable</th>
          <th>Use</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--empty-state-max-width</code></td>
          <td>The text measure. The block centers in its region and wraps text to this width.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--empty-state-padding-block</code></td>
          <td>Vertical padding around the block. The compact modifier lowers it.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--empty-state-padding-inline</code></td>
          <td>Horizontal padding around the block.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--empty-state-gap</code></td>
          <td>Space between the title and the text.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--empty-state-media-gap</code></td>
          <td>Space below the media, before the title.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--empty-state-action-gap</code></td>
          <td>Space above the action row.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Media</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Variable</th>
          <th>Use</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--empty-state-media-size</code></td>
          <td>Diameter of the default media circle.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--empty-state-icon-size</code></td>
          <td>Size of a bare glyph inside the default media.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--empty-state-art-size</code></td>
          <td>Maximum width of a paired illustration or image.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--empty-state-tone</code></td>
          <td>Media fill, tint, and glyph color. The tone modifiers set this, and an inline value wins for one block.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <h3>Bordered</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Variable</th>
          <th>Use</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--empty-state-border-color</code></td>
          <td>Dashed edge color. Follows the tone by default.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--empty-state-radius</code></td>
          <td>Corner radius of the bordered box.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--empty-state-bg</code></td>
          <td>Fill of the bordered box. Transparent by default.</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>
{% endblock %}
